        </div>
        <h6 class="mt-4">2. Non-Deterministic Finite Automaton (NFA)</h6>
        <ul>
            <li>For a state and input symbol, multiple transitions (or none) are allowed.</li>
            <li>Can have epsilon (empty string, ε) transitions.</li>
            <li>Accepts the input if any path leads to a final state.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="alert alert-info mt-2 p-3 rounded">
            <h6>NFA Example:</h6>
            <p>Accepts strings ending with 'a' over Σ={a,b}:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><b>States:</b> Q={q₀, q₁}</li>
                <li><b>Alphabet:</b> Σ={a,b}</li>
                <li><b>Start State:</b> q₀</li>
                <li><b>Final State:</b> F={q₁}</li>
            </ul>
            <h6>Transition Table:</h6>
            <div class="table-responsive bg-dark p-2 rounded">
                <table class="table table-bordered table-sm text-white">
                    <thead class="table-light">
                        <tr><th>State</th><th>a</th><th>b</th></tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr><td>q0</td><td>{q0,q1}</td><td>q0</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>q1</td><td>∅</td><td>∅</td></tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
            <h6 class="mt-4">NFA Diagram: Strings Ending with 'a'</h6>
            <div id="nfaEndingWithAVisualization" class="mt-2" style="height: 300px; border: 1px solid #ccc;"></div>
